nds that different Japanese leaders have shaped Japanese diplomacy in some important and underappreciated ways. In certain environments, individual difference has played a significant role in determining Japan's diplomacy, both in terms of the country's strategic identity and summit diplomacy. What emerges from Japanese Diplomacy, therefore, is a more nuanced overall picture of Japanese leadership in foreign affairs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aPersonality and politics. 0aPolitical leadershipxJapan. 0aPolitical leadershipzJapan. 0aPrime ministersxJapan. 0aPrime ministerszJapan. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Japanese Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : International Relations. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Diplomacy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2015z978311149061840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438454993423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438454993/original  a978-3-11-149061-8  SUNY Press eBook Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles